frameDefinitions: An Agent causes a Dryee (either a surface or an entire entity, inside and out) to become dry.
An Entity loses moisture with the outcome of being in a dry state.
A Lessor who owns some Goods allows a Lessee to use the Goods temporarily in exchange for Money.
A Killer or Cause causes the death of the Victim.
An Item is in a state of dryness.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person performing the intentional act causing the <fen>Dryee</fen> to become dry.
The <fen>Dryee</fen> is the entity which has the water removed from it.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces the state of dryness. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> intentionally affects the <fen>Dryee</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> intentionally affects the <fen>Dryee</fen>.
The <fen>Entity</fen> is the thing that loses moisture and becomes dry.
When the <fen>Entity</fen> becomes dry.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> becomes dry.
The <fen>Lessee</fen> has <fen>Money</fen> and wants the <fen>Goods</fen>.
The role <fen>Goods</fen> is the item which is temporarily exchanged for <fen>Money</fen>.
The <fen>Lessor</fen> has possession of the <fen>Goods</fen> and temporarily exchanges them for <fen>Money</fen> from a <fen>Lessee</fen>.
The time at which the renting takes place.
The location where the leasing takes place.
The person or sentient entity that causes the death of the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The living entity that dies as a result of the killing.
An inanimate entity or process that causes the death of the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The method or action that the <fen>Killer</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen> performs resulting in the death of the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The device used by the <fen>Killer</fen> to bring about the death of the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The point or period of time within which the <fen>Victim</fen> is killed.
The location where the death took place.
The <fen>Item</fen> exists in a state of dryness.
